events.description:
You Can Dance to Make a Difference!
OLD SCHOOL DANCE FUNDRAISER
80's, R&B, Disco, Dusties, Steppin' & House!
The Young Masterbuilders in Motion, Inc., (YMIM) a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, is hosting an Old School Dance to raise funds to support young adult women orphans, adoptees, and foster youth alumnae. Our participants have aged out of foster care and are enrolled or seeking to enroll in a high-demand trade school certification program, or in a college degree seeking program. 
Join us for great music, board and card games, and LINE DANCE LESSONS for a great cause!
Helping our young adult women who are foster youth alumnae is critically important. According to the National Foster Youth Institute, after reaching the age of 18, 20% of the children who were in foster care will become instantly homeless. Only 1 out of every 2 foster youth will have some form of gainful employment by the age of 24. There is less than a 3% chance for children who have aged out of foster care to earn a college degree at any point in their life.
Although, those facts are startling, together we can reverse the impact of poverty through educating young women who are foster youth alumnae.
Learn more about us by visiting the Young Masterbuilders in Motion website at https://www.theymim.org
Thank you in advance for your support. And remember, if your employer offers matching funds, your contribution doubles! 
For now, just get your dance shoes ready and meet us on the dance floor soon!
Kim Wright, MBA, U.S. Army Veteran
Founder, Foster Youth Alumna
Young Masterbuilders in Motion, Inc.
Learn more about us at www.theymim.org
Call us at 773.941.1200.

FAQs
 
Are there ID or minimum age requirements to enter the event?
The Broadway Armory provides safety officers while the facility is open. For this event, attendees must show ID and be age 21 and over. Your attendance at this event will likely be captured in photos. Attending the event grants consent for your image to be used in publicity for the nonprofit marketing purposes..
 
What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Metered street parking, and Divvy bike parking are available. Nearby public transportation is via the CTA Broadway 36 bus line or the CTA Redline Thorndale station. 
What can I bring into the event?
Your bright smile. Comfortable dance apparel and shoes. Your friends and family you want to hang out with laughing and having fun. Your card or board game to play when you want to sit down after so much dancing! Bring business cards for networking. 
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Founder@theymim.org 
What's the refund policy?
Refunds are not available. 
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Yes, you must bring your printed ticket to the event for admission, wifi is not available. Mobile signal transmission will likely be unreliable. 
Can I update my registration information?
No 
Is my registration fee or ticket transferrable?
 No
Is it ok if the name on my ticket or registration doesn't match the person who attends?
No
